  "text": "Notice that, in this formula, F is considered as an S \u221e -invariant function on (R d ) N . Since F is bounded, so is the function P t F , and we only have to prove the continuity. To this end, let \u03b3 j \u2192 \u03b3 in the \u03c1 metric. By Lemma 4.1 in [CITATION_1] , there always exists a representative (",
